NUMBER 253
NAME Main Street
MONSTER_GROUP 1
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Large buildings, featureless in the gray light, loom around you here midway between the bazaar and Fayd's downtown district. People crowd past you on important business, and you feel small and insignificant among so many in such a hurry.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT E 254
EXIT W 252
EXIT ABOVE 2152
IFENTRY
	IFVAR INTNUM6 = 2
		ECHO PLAYER A commoner approaches you helpfully, "You look like the adventuring type, you should go to the Adventurers' Guild west of here."
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 298
NAME Adventurers' Guild
FIXED_LIGHT
DEEPCAVE
*DESCRIPTION_START
The Adventurers' Guild is the oldest organization in Fayd. It was founded with the hope that adventurers would provide a better protection from the evils of the world than any organized military. The government provides free training to newcomers. A dark stairway leads down to the Test Tunnels, a proving ground for new adventurers in the Realms.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 275
ITEM 0 1226 VAL2=225
IFENTRY
	IFVAR INTNUM6 = 2
		ECHO PLAYER The guildmaster greets you as you arrive at the Adventurers' Guild for the first time. [Type TRAIN to see what training is available!]
		AWARD 4 100
		EQUAL INTNUM6 3
	ENDIF
ENDIF
